Preconditions:
- The input grid must be a 2D matrix of size m x n.
- The grid must be 0-indexed.
- Each cell in the grid can either be a land cell (0) or a water cell containing fish (greater than 0).
- The grid can have multiple water cells.

Postconditions:
- The method should return an integer representing the maximum number of fish the fisher can catch.
- If there are no water cells in the grid, the method should return 0.
- The fisher can start at any water cell and catch all the fish at that cell.
- The fisher can move to any adjacent water cell.
- The fisher can perform the above operations any number of times.